CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1784767668
OL,3,CWorld Cup demand boosts pubs but
OL,4,Crestaurant and bar sales stumble
OL,6,FKarl Chessell, director for
OL,7,Fhospitality operators and food at NIQ,
OL,8,Fsaid: "June's numbers complete a
OL,9,Fmodest first half of the year for
OL,10,Fhospitality in which any real-terms
OL,11,Fgrowth was very hard-earned.
OL,13,F"The combination of the World Cup and
OL,14,Fsunshine was a boost to pubs, and we
OL,15,Fcan expect strong July results after
OL,16,FEngland's progress in the tournament.
OL,18,F"However, big events and the heat tend
OL,19,Fto work less well for restaurants, who
OL,20,Fare besieged by high costs at the
OL,21,Fmoment."
